+## Plan Must Be Executable By The Weakest Model (HARD RULE)
+
+- A plan is not notes for a smart agent. It is rails for the stupidest LLM that can follow instructions.
+- The bar is pathological specificity: exact files, exact line anchors, exact tests, exact red failures, exact source shapes, exact commands, exact success evidence, and exact stop conditions.
+- If an implementer can fill a gap with vibes, the plan failed. Patch the plan before coding.
+- Red-team plans ruthlessly before execution. Every criticism must become concrete plan text, not a chat-only warning.
+- Never hand a plan to execution until a tired junior dev at 3am could complete it without asking a question.
+
+## Improve The Compiler As You Go (HARD RULE)
+
+- Every app-building failure is compiler evidence, not just an app bug.
+- When an app exposes a repeated footgun, add a compiler test and fix the compiler in the same plan.
+- Do not paper over bad generated code by hand-patching generated output or adding app-local ceremony.
+- If the Clear source had to say something obvious, ask whether the compiler should infer, validate, or generate it.
+- The goal is fewer future mistakes from weaker models, not just one prettier demo.
+
