 checkout gets it. The compiler is a library of correct patterns that grows every
 time we build something. Without Clear, every app starts from zero.
 
+**Fluid intelligence becomes crystallized intelligence.** LLMs are fluid
+intelligence: slow, improvisational, expensive, and conscious. Clear squeezes
+that intelligence into a crystal: readable source, deterministic compiler rules,
+tests, examples, and hardened runtime patterns. It is the same shift as learning
+piano. At first, every note is deliberate. After enough practice, the pattern
+moves into muscle memory. Clear is how AI work moves from "think through this
+from scratch" into "replay the proven pattern fast." The more real apps we build,
+test, and repair through Clear, the stronger the crystal gets.
+
+**Discipline must become machinery.** A rule in a prompt is fluid intelligence:
+the model has to remember it, care about it, and apply it under pressure. A
+gate in the repo is crystallized intelligence: it runs the same way every time,
+even when the model is tired, rushed, or too confident. Clear's operating system
+should therefore turn every painful miss into a script, compiler check, generated
+test, hook, or lint rule. Skills are the front door. They teach the workflow.
+Programmatic gates are the lock. They make the workflow hard to skip.
+
 **The human can put AI in a loop.** Write Clear, compile, test, fix compiler,
 repeat. No human needed for the mechanical parts. The compiler gets better
 autonomously through adversarial use. Point AI at "build an ecom app" and come
